the Dresden Codex. Macri compares some particles in Classic-period inscriptions from different sites to show that it may be possible to group sites in terms of lan­guage variation. A number of interesting papers com­bine iconographic and architectural analyses to better our understanding of aspects of high-ranking lineage organization at Palenque (Schele), Chichen Itzii (Krochock), and Copan (Fash), the symbolic impor­tance of stelae at Late Classic Yaxchilim (Tate), and the significance of ritual in inscriptions and architec­tural alignments (Aveni). 
